oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Elvis Presley and the Jordanaires meet Gov. Buford Ellington
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Elvis Presley and the Jordanaires visit Gov. Buford Ellington at the Tennessee State Capitol. The Jordanaires are accompanied by their wives, while Gov. Ellington's daughter Ann stands to the left of Elvis. Pictured (L-R): Jean Stoker, Gordon Stoker, Charlsie Matthews, Neal Matthews, Ann Ellington (later Ann Ellington Wagner), Elvis Presley, Dot Hawkins, Gov Buford Ellington, Hoyt Hawkins, Marilyn Walker, Ray Walker.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: RG 82: Tennessee Department of Conservation Photograph Collection, 1937-1976
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Singers; Musicians; Entertainers; Governors
